FBIS3-55878 "drsov008_c_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 Federal Assembly Shumeyko To Quit Government Post If Elected Speaker LD1101180294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1700 GMT 11 Jan 94 LD1101180294 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] Federation Council deputies today drew up a ballot paper for the election of the chairman of the upper chamber of parliament. [passage omitted] In order to be elected speaker of the Federation Council, it is necessary to receive 86 votes, INTERFAX points out. In an interview with that agency, Vladimir Shumeyko declared that, if elected, he will leave the post of first vice premier of the Russian Government. According to Shumeyko, a decision will soon be adopted in the Federation Council according to which the leadership of the chamber, unlke ordinary deputies, will operate on a permanent basis.
